│ correctly.                                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ 2. `evaluate-call-errors.ll` expects "Signature mismatch." for a ptr-to-i32 │
│ case, but my void-specific fix doesn't handle that.                         │
│                                                                             │
│ But the original bug report specifically mentions a void-to-non-void        │
│ scenario.                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me look at the stack trace one more time:                               │
│                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                         │
│ #16 0x000074931ac73427 (anonymous                                           │
│ namespace)::ConstantFoldConstantImpl(llvm::Constant const*,                 │
│ llvm::DataLayout const&, llvm::TargetLibraryInfo const*,                    │
│ llvm::SmallDenseMap<llvm::Constant*, llvm::Constant*, 4u,                   │
│ llvm::DenseMapInfo<llvm::Constant*, void>,                                  │
│ llvm::detail::DenseMapPair<llvm::Constant*, llvm::Constant*>>&)             │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/ConstantFolding.cpp:1087:7                                │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ The crash is in `ConstantFoldConstantImpl` when doing `isa<ConstantVector>` │
│ on a null pointer.                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ This happens because `InstResult` is null.                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ In the reproducer:                                                          │
│ - `__cxa_guard_acquire` returns void                                        │
│ - It's called as i32                                                        │
│ - `RetVal` is null                                                          │
│ - `InstResult = castCallResultIfNeeded(i32, null)` returns null             │
│ - The code continues because the original check `if (RetVal &&              │
│ !InstResult)` is false (RetVal is null)                                     │
│ - Later, `InstResult` (null) is passed to `ConstantFoldConstant`, causing   │
│ the crash                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ So the fix must ensure that when `RetVal` is null and the call type is      │
│ non-void, we return false.                                                  │
